This technique removes [[seal]]s that are of similar power to itself. The user gathers [[chakra]] to their fingertips and hits the fingers against the seal that is to be removed, causing it to unravel and disappear. If the seal was applied to a person, the thrust of the hand that accompanies this technique will likely be painful. When [[Jiraiya]] uses this technique to remove a [[Five Elements Seal]], it appears to be quite easy for him. In truth, this is a very advanced technique that even [[jōnin]] would find difficult to perform.<ref name="d1"/>

In the anime, [[Kazuma]] uses the Five Elements Unseal on [[Sora]], thus increasing his access to the [[Nine-Tails]]' chakra sealed in his body.<ref>''Naruto: Shippūden'' episode 61</ref> In another episode, [[Orochimaru]] uses the Five Elements Unseal to break the [[Iron Armour Seal]].<ref>''Naruto: Shippūden'' episode 318</ref>

== Trivia ==
* In the anime, Orochimaru stated that only his fellow [[Sannin]] and [[Hiruzen Sarutobi]] could perform this technique.<ref>''Naruto'' episode 94</ref>
* When Jiraiya performs this technique, the "Five Elements" referred to in the name are the Chinese Five Elements, the {{translation|''Five Movements''|五行|Japanese: Gogyō, Chinese: Wǔxíng}}:
:# {{translation|Metal|金| ''Chinese:'' jīn}}
:# {{translation|Wood|木| ''Chinese:'' mù}}
:# {{translation|Water|水| ''Chinese:'' shuǐ}}
:# {{translation|Fire|火| ''Chinese:'' huǒ}}
:# {{translation|Earth|土| ''Chinese:'' tǔ}}
*When [[Kazuma]] performs this technique on [[Sora]], the five elements are shown as the five [[Nature Transformation|chakra elements]] used in most other techniques, the {{translation|''Five Greats''|五大|Godai}}:
:# {{translation|Earth|土|tsuchi}}
:# {{translation|Water|水|mizu}}
:# {{translation|Fire|火|hi}}
:# {{translation|Wind|風|kaze}}
:# {{translation|Lightning|雷|kaminari}}
